By BO Staff Writer Dr Nchaupe Aubrey Mokoape, Cde Tiyani Lybon Mabasa, and Prof Itumeleng Mosala – you can’t miss this outstanding lineup of Black Consciousness Movement (BCM) panelists who will tonight be discussing the location of the June 16, 1976 moment in the history of South Africa. The discussion will be streamed live via Zoom on Andile Mngxitama’s “Blacks Can’t Be Racist” Facebook page. Mngxitama is the President of the radical black consciousness organization, Black First Land First (BLF). Check the details of the event in the featured poster. Black Power Salute!!!